<subSubSection id="C3219E90687CFFF4FF25107CFE1BF92C" pageId="6" pageNumber="353" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B84CD1B687CFFF4FF25107CFE1BF92C" blockId="6.[151,1437,582,1723]" pageId="6" pageNumber="353">
<emphasis id="B94F1109687CFFF4FF25107CFEBDF900" bold="true" box="[199,326,1662,1687]" pageId="6" pageNumber="353">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="B94F1109687CFFF4FC92107CFC48F901" box="[880,947,1662,1686]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="353">longi-</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B94F1109687CFFF4FC11107DFBC7F901" box="[1011,1084,1663,1686]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="353">ovatus</emphasis>
, referring to the shape of the gnathos in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
